38#include "der_locl.h"
39#include <krb5/heim_asn1.h>
40
41__RCSID("$NetBSD: extra.c,v 1.2 2017/01/28 21:31:45 christos Exp $");
42
43int
44encode_heim_any(unsigned char *p, size_t len,
45 const heim_any *data, size_t *size)
46{
47 return der_put_octet_string (p, len, data, size);
48}
49
50int
51decode_heim_any(const unsigned char *p, size_t len,
52 heim_any *data, size_t *size)
53{
54 size_t len_len, length, l;
55 Der_class thisclass;
56 Der_type thistype;
57 unsigned int thistag;
58 int e;
59
60 memset(data, 0, sizeof(*data));
61
62 e = der_get_tag (p, len, &thisclass, &thistype, &thistag, &l);
63 if (e) return e;
64 if (l > len)
65 return ASN1_OVERFLOW;
66 e = der_get_length(p + l, len - l, &length, &len_len);
67 if (e) return e;
68 if (length == ASN1_INDEFINITE) {
69 if (len < len_len + l)
70 return ASN1_OVERFLOW;
71 length = len - (len_len + l);
72 } else {
73 if (len < length + len_len + l)
74 return ASN1_OVERFLOW;
75 }
76
77 data->data = malloc(length + len_len + l);
78 if (data->data == NULL)
79 return ENOMEM;
80 data->length = length + len_len + l;
81 memcpy(data->data, p, length + len_len + l);
82
83 if (size)
84 *size = length + len_len + l;
85
86 return 0;
87}
88
89void
90free_heim_any(heim_any *data)
91{
92 der_free_octet_string(data);
93}
94
95size_t
96length_heim_any(const heim_any *data)
97{
98 return data->length;
99}
100
101int
102copy_heim_any(const heim_any *from, heim_any *to)
103{
104 return der_copy_octet_string(from, to);
105}
106
107int
108encode_heim_any_set(unsigned char *p, size_t len,
109 const heim_any_set *data, size_t *size)
110{
111 return der_put_octet_string (p, len, data, size);
112}
113
114int
115decode_heim_any_set(const unsigned char *p, size_t len,
116 heim_any_set *data, size_t *size)
117{
118 return der_get_octet_string(p, len, data, size);
119}
120
121void
122free_heim_any_set(heim_any_set *data)
123{
124 der_free_octet_string(data);
125}
126
127size_t
128length_heim_any_set(const heim_any *data)
129{
130 return data->length;
131}
132
133int
134copy_heim_any_set(const heim_any_set *from, heim_any_set *to)
135{
136 return der_copy_octet_string(from, to);
137}
138
139int
140heim_any_cmp(const heim_any_set *p, const heim_any_set *q)
141{
142 return der_heim_octet_string_cmp(p, q);
143}
